result.execSummary:
The defendant Christina E Jester was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Christina E Jester in court with attorney Gregory Allen Gerbers.  Defendant Christina E Jester in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Ct. 2.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of Ct. 2. Court dismisses Ct. 1 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Attorney Gregory Allen Gerbers in court.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file. Atty Gerbers has no comment. State requests bench warrant. Court orders bench warrant.

Defendant Christina E Jester appears by phone along with attorney Gregory Allen Gerbers who appears in person.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file, questions defendant why she's not in court in person.  Defendant indicates she is dealing with some medical issues with family and wasn't able to make it to court today. Atty Gerbers now has discovery, needs to review that information with defendant and talk to her about the State's offer. Defense requests another date for status/possible plea.  State asks court to set plea date today so defendant has plenty of time to make arrangement to appear. Court advises defendant she needs to appear in person for next hearing. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for May 10, 2016 at 11:45 am.

Status conference scheduled for March 18, 2016 at 10:45 am.
